cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with bibliometric indicators and normalization techniques for comparing publications from different scientific fields and years. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses on the analysis of citation data, we consider cs.DL and cs.IR to be the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CY, cs.SI, and cs.CR.
